DETAILED CONTENT

1. Purpose and core actionable rules
- Location: ./SOURCES.md at repository root. Only this file is consumed by the maintain-library workflow.
- Line handling: ignore blank lines and lines starting with '#'. Treat remaining lines as source entries.

2. Source formatting and metadata fields
- Required: absolute URL (HTTPS strongly preferred).
- Optional metadata: fields separated by tabs. Supported fields in order: title, tags (comma-separated), retrieval_date (ISO 8601), content_type (MIME), notes.
- Example canonical entry format (no quoting, single-line): https://example.org/docs/api.html<TAB>Example API Docs<TAB>api,reference

3. Normalization and deduplication
- Normalization steps before dedup check:
  a) Lowercase scheme and host.
  b) Remove trailing slash from path.
  c) Strip common tracking query parameters: utm_*, fbclid, gclid, ref, ref_src.
  d) Percent-decode path segments where safe, then re-encode minimal necessary characters.
- Deduplication: check normalized URL against library documents' recorded source_url metadata; if match, update existing document instead of creating a new file.

4. Maintain-library processing behavior
- Fetch policy: GET request with Accept: text/*, application/json, application/pdf; follow redirects up to 5 hops; timeout 30s.
- Retries: up to 3 attempts with exponential backoff (initial delay 1s, then 2s, then 4s).
- Content extraction: for HTML, extract visible text and metadata (title, meta description, canonical link); for JSON, save raw JSON and extract top-level keys; for PDF, run text extraction; for other binary types, store metadata and raw bytes only.
- Output files: placed under library/ with filename pattern: {HOSTNAME}__{SLUG}{.ext}. Record metadata header in the file top with keys: source_url, retrieval_date (ISO 8601), content_type, content_length_bytes, sha256_hex.
- Metadata persistence: maintain a manifest index file library/manifest.json mapping source_url -> document filename, last_retrieved, size, sha256.

5. Configuration values and their exact effects
- agentic-lib.toml [paths].library = "library/" defines where output documents are written.
- agentic-lib.toml [paths].library-sources = "SOURCES.md" defines source list path.
- agentic-lib.toml [limits].library-limit = 32 enforces the maximum number of library documents; the workflow will abort new additions beyond this limit.
- agentic-lib.toml [execution] commands (build/test/start) are informational; they do not change how sources are processed by maintain-library.

6. Fetching and error-handling requirements
- HTTP status handling: 200 OK proceeds; 3xx handled by redirect policy; 4xx records permanent failure (no retry beyond configured attempts); 5xx retried up to retry limit.
- Invalid content type: if Content-Type is absent or unexpected, inspect response body first 512 bytes; if binary, store raw and set content_type=application/octet-stream.
- Large files: if content-length > 10 MiB, store only metadata and a 2 MiB sample unless explicit override is present in metadata.
- Failure remediation: log error with URL, HTTP status, final URL after redirects, error message, and timestamp. Add a retrieval_note in manifest.

7. Best practices for source selection
- Prefer canonical or raw documentation pages (direct API docs, raw spec files, GitHub raw files) over landing pages.
- Include explicit titles and tags when possible to aid downstream categorization.
- Avoid private or paywalled links unless credentials are managed by CI secrets; workflows will not accept credentials from SOURCES.md.

8. Troubleshooting steps and remediation
- If a source is unreachable: confirm URL, test with curl from CI runner, check robots.txt and rate limits.
- If duplicate documents are created: verify normalization rules and clean existing manifest entries; update the existing library doc rather than adding a new source line.
- If the library-limit is reached: remove stale or low-value entries from SOURCES.md and library/manifest.json, then re-run the workflow.

